author: Inside Edition
description: These birds set their nests up in strange places. In 2017, a pigeon made herself at home in a colander in the kitchen of a New York City woman's apartment. In 2023, a mama bird laid her eggs on the 25-yard line of a Huntington Beach, California, high school football field. In 2017, a pair of wild geese nested their eggs in an empty flower pot outside of the emergency room and maternity ward of a Nebraska Hospital. Inside Edition Digital's Andrea Swindall has more.
title: Birds That Set Their Nests Up in Strange Places
